         <abstract>
            <p>
               Periodic Hermite spline interpolants on an equidistant lattice are represented by the Bézier technique as well as by the B-spline method. Circulant matrices are used to derive new explicit formulas for the periodic Hermite splines of degree m and defect r (1 ≤ r ≤ m). Applying the known de Casteljau algorithm and the de Boor algorithm, respectively, we obtain new efficient real algorithms for periodic Hermite spline interpolation. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
